canonical:
  title: 爲綾城倅賀羅州太守到官狀
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 分萬乘之憂與民爲母制一方之命於我是天恭惟某官奉綍九門專城百里穎川作雨不害爲傅說之霖南國茇棠行必闢孫弘之閣州符暫屈台陛當信某蕞爾庸資庇于仁蔭自惟拙政懵緩急於事機仰止上官寄死生於威化
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 爲綾城倅賀羅州太守到官狀
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 分萬乘之憂。與民爲母。制一方之命。於我是天。恭惟某官。奉綍九門。專城百里。穎川作雨。不害爲傅說之霖。南國茇棠。行必闢孫弘之閣。州符暫屈。台陛當信。某蕞爾庸資。庇于仁蔭。自惟拙政。懵緩急於事機。仰止上官。寄死生於威化。
korean:
  title: 위 능성쉬 하 나주태수 도관 장
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 임금의 근심을 나눠 맡았으니 백성의 어머니가 되었고, 한 지방의 명령을 전제하니 나에게는 바로 하늘과 같습니다. 삼가 생각하건대, 모관(某官)은 대궐에서 조서(詔書)를 받들고, 백 리의 고을을 맡아 다스리니, 영천(穎川)에서 비를 내리게 한 것은 부열(傅說)의 임(霖)이 될 수 있고, 남국(南國)에서 아가위나무 그늘에 쉰 것은[茇棠] 장차 공손홍(公孫弘)의 각(閣)을 마련할 것입니다. 지방 수령으로 잠깐 좌천되었으니 마땅히 조정의 재상으로 승진될 줄 믿습니다. 모(某)는 못생긴 용렬한 자질로 어지신 그늘에 의지하고 있으니, 스스로 돌이켜 볼 때 졸렬한 정책이 사리의 선후에 몽매하니, 상관(上官)의 권위와 덕화에 죽고 삶을 맡길 따름입니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0510_010_0470&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Congratulatory Statement on the Arrival at Office of the Governor of Naju, Appointed as Deputy of Neungseong
  author: Lee Kyubo
  language: eng
  text: You share the burdens that weigh upon the throne, becoming a mother to the people. You command the destiny of an entire region, which to me is like heaven itself. I humbly consider how you receive the imperial decree within the palace halls and oversee governance of these hundred leagues. The rains you bring to Yingchuan rival those of Fushuò—a blessing upon the land. The shade beneath the parasol tree in the southern realm shall surely prepare the way for your ascent, as once it did for Gongsun Hong. Though you are but briefly stationed in this provincial post, the court shall surely recognize your merit and call you to higher station. As for myself, a humble and untalented creature, I shelter beneath your generous shadow. Reflecting upon my own inadequate governance, I remain clouded in discerning the urgencies of affairs. I can only look upward to your authority and virtue, entrusting both my life and death to your transformative influence.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Fushuò (傅說) was a legendary sage minister who brought timely rains and blessings to his realm, used here as a metaphor for excellent governance.
  - key: ''
    value: Gongsun Hong (公孫弘) was a Han dynasty official who rose from humble provincial service to become Chancellor, suggesting the recipient's promising future advancement.
  - key: ''
    value: The parasol tree (茇棠) is a classical symbol of worthy officials finding proper recognition.
